{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We've been told to go out on a limb\nand say something surprising."},{"time":5786,"text":"So I'll try and do that,"},{"time":7000,"text":"but I want to start with two things\nthat everyone already knows."},{"time":13520,"text":"And the first one, in fact,\nis something that has been known"},{"time":16805,"text":"for most of recorded history,"},{"time":20000,"text":"and that is, that the planet Earth,\nor the solar system,"},{"time":24883,"text":"or our environment or whatever,"},{"time":27829,"text":"is uniquely suited\nto sustain our evolution --"},{"time":34144,"text":"or creation, as it used to be thought --"},{"time":37000,"text":"and our present existence,\nand most important, our future survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44176,"text":"Nowadays, this idea\nhas a dramatic name: Spaceship Earth."},{"time":48819,"text":"And the idea there\nis that outside the spaceship,"},{"time":51358,"text":"the universe is implacably hostile,"},{"time":54402,"text":"and inside is all we have,\nall we depend on,"},{"time":58270,"text":"and we only get the one chance:\nif we mess up our spaceship,"},{"time":61420,"text":"we've got nowhere else to go."},{"time":63293,"text":"Now, the second thing\nthat everyone already knows"},{"time":66124,"text":"is that, contrary to what was believed\nfor most of human history,"},{"time":71593,"text":"human beings are not, in fact,\nthe hub of existence."},{"time":77336,"text":"As Stephen Hawking famously said,"},{"time":79676,"text":"we're just a chemical scum\non the surface of a typical planet"},{"time":84596,"text":"that's in orbit around a typical star,"},{"time":86906,"text":"which is on the outskirts\nof a typical galaxy, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91883,"text":"Now, the first of those two things\nthat everyone knows is kind of saying"},{"time":96805,"text":"that we're at a very un-typical place,\nuniquely suited and so on,"},{"time":101466,"text":"and the second one is saying\nthat we're at a typical place."},{"time":104950,"text":"And, especially if you regard\nthese two as deep truths to live by"},{"time":109835,"text":"and to inform your life decisions,"},{"time":112000,"text":"then they seem a little bit\nto conflict with each other."},{"time":118480,"text":"But that doesn't prevent them\nfrom both being completely false."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123861,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":125266,"text":"And they are."},{"time":127189,"text":"So let me start with the second one:"},{"time":133070,"text":"\"Typical.\" Well, is this a typical place?"},{"time":137175,"text":"Well, let's look around, you know,\nlook in a random direction,"},{"time":140164,"text":"and we see a wall, and chemical scum --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145777,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"and that's not typical\nof the universe at all."},{"time":151852,"text":"All you've got to do is go\na few hundred miles in that same direction"},{"time":155299,"text":"and look back,"},{"time":156494,"text":"and you won't see any walls\nor chemical scum at all --"},{"time":159848,"text":"all you see is a blue planet."},{"time":161579,"text":"And if you go further than that,"},{"time":164208,"text":"you'll see the Sun, the solar system\nand the stars and so on,"},{"time":168614,"text":"but that's still not typical\nof the universe,"},{"time":170769,"text":"because stars come in galaxies."},{"time":174117,"text":"And most places in the universe,\na typical place in the universe,"},{"time":178919,"text":"is nowhere near any galaxies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"So let's go out further, till we're\noutside the galaxy, and look back,"},{"time":186551,"text":"and yeah, there's the huge galaxy\nwith spiral arms laid out in front of us."},{"time":192266,"text":"And at this point, we've come\n100,000 light-years from here."},{"time":198394,"text":"But we're still nowhere near\na typical place in the universe."},{"time":203000,"text":"To get to a typical place,"},{"time":204773,"text":"you've got to go\n1,000 times as far as that,"},{"time":209314,"text":"into intergalactic space."},{"time":211870,"text":"And so, what does that\nlook like -- \"typical?\""},{"time":214937,"text":"What does a \"typical\" place\nin the universe look like?"},{"time":217510,"text":"Well, at enormous expense,\nTED has arranged"},{"time":221544,"text":"a high-resolution immersion\nvirtual reality rendering"},{"time":226626,"text":"of the view from intergalactic space."},{"time":230000,"text":"Can we have the lights off,\nplease, so we can see it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"Well, not quite, not quite perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241390,"text":"You see, intergalactic space\nis completely dark, pitch dark."},{"time":248095,"text":"It's so dark,"},{"time":250002,"text":"that if you were to be looking\nat the nearest star to you,"},{"time":255692,"text":"and that star were to explode\nas a supernova,"},{"time":259814,"text":"and you were to be staring directly at it\nat the moment when its light reached you,"},{"time":264726,"text":"you still wouldn't be able\nto see even a glimmer."},{"time":268667,"text":"That's how big and how dark\nthe universe is."},{"time":271786,"text":"And that's despite the fact\nthat a supernova is so bright,"},{"time":276571,"text":"so brilliant an event,"},{"time":279045,"text":"that it would kill you stone dead\nat a range of several light-years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283306,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284949,"text":"And yet, from intergalactic space,"},{"time":286888,"text":"it's so far away you wouldn't even see it."},{"time":289347,"text":"It's also very cold out there --"},{"time":292000,"text":"less than three degrees\nabove absolute zero."},{"time":295553,"text":"And it's very empty."},{"time":297435,"text":"The vacuum there is one million times\nless dense than the highest vacuum"},{"time":303300,"text":"that our best technology on Earth\ncan currently create."},{"time":306645,"text":"So that's how different\na typical place is from this place."},{"time":313000,"text":"And that is how un-typical this place is."},{"time":316151,"text":"So can we have the lights\nback on please? Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321262,"text":"Now, how do we know about an environment\nthat's so far away and so different"},{"time":326628,"text":"and so alien from anything we're used to?"},{"time":329699,"text":"Well, the Earth -- our environment,\nin the form of us --"},{"time":333089,"text":"is creating knowledge."},{"time":335139,"text":"Well, what does that mean?"},{"time":336503,"text":"Well, look out even further\nthan we've just been --"},{"time":340000,"text":"I mean from here, with a telescope --"},{"time":342324,"text":"and you'll see things that look\nlike stars, they're called quasars."},{"time":346522,"text":"\"Quasars\" originally meant\n\"quasi-stellar object,\""},{"time":349759,"text":"which means \"things that look\na bit like stars.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":352526,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353835,"text":"But they're not stars."},{"time":355213,"text":"And we know what they are."},{"time":359478,"text":"Billions of years ago\nand billions of light-years away,"},{"time":362853,"text":"the material at the center\nof a galaxy collapsed"},{"time":367000,"text":"towards a super-massive black hole."},{"time":369395,"text":"And then intense magnetic fields"},{"time":371701,"text":"directed some of the energy\nof that gravitational collapse"},{"time":375671,"text":"and some of the matter"},{"time":377000,"text":"back out in the form of tremendous jets,"},{"time":379123,"text":"which illuminated lobes"},{"time":380981,"text":"with the brilliance of --\nI think it's a trillion -- suns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387886,"text":"Now, the physics of the human brain\ncould hardly be more unlike"},{"time":392422,"text":"the physics of such a jet."},{"time":394369,"text":"We couldn't survive for an instant in it."},{"time":396745,"text":"Language breaks down\nwhen trying to describe"},{"time":399778,"text":"what it would be like\nin one of those jets."},{"time":402000,"text":"It would be a bit like experiencing\na supernova explosion,"},{"time":405082,"text":"but at point-blank range\nand for millions of years at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408623,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412174,"text":"And yet, that jet happened\nin precisely such a way"},{"time":418288,"text":"that billions of years later,\non the other side of the universe,"},{"time":422032,"text":"some bit of chemical scum\ncould accurately describe"},{"time":426198,"text":"and model and predict\nand explain, above all --"},{"time":430212,"text":"there's your reference --"},{"time":432362,"text":"what was happening there, in reality."},{"time":436572,"text":"The one physical system, the brain,\ncontains an accurate working model"},{"time":441331,"text":"of the other, the quasar."},{"time":443203,"text":"Not just a superficial image of it,\nthough it contains that as well,"},{"time":446802,"text":"but an explanatory model,"},{"time":448807,"text":"embodying the same\nmathematical relationships"},{"time":451878,"text":"and the same causal structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454330,"text":"Now, that is knowledge."},{"time":456983,"text":"And if that weren't amazing enough,"},{"time":459000,"text":"the faithfulness with which\nthe one structure resembles the other"},{"time":463000,"text":"is increasing with time."},{"time":465107,"text":"That is the growth of knowledge."},{"time":467604,"text":"So, the laws of physics\nhave this special property,"},{"time":471000,"text":"that physical objects as unlike each other\nas they could possibly be,"},{"time":475781,"text":"can nevertheless embody the same\nmathematical and causal structure"},{"time":481549,"text":"and to do it more and more so over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485068,"text":"So we are a chemical scum\nthat is different."},{"time":488264,"text":"This chemical scum has universality."},{"time":491842,"text":"Its structure contains,\nwith ever-increasing precision,"},{"time":496272,"text":"the structure of everything."},{"time":497726,"text":"This place, and not other places\nin the universe,"},{"time":501454,"text":"is a hub which contains within itself\nthe structural and causal essence"},{"time":507554,"text":"of the whole of the rest\nof physical reality."},{"time":510315,"text":"And so, far from being insignificant,"},{"time":512187,"text":"the fact that the laws\nof physics allow this"},{"time":514915,"text":"or even mandate that this can happen,"},{"time":518390,"text":"is one of the most important things\nabout the physical world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523355,"text":"Now how does the solar system --\nour environment, in the form of us --"},{"time":528667,"text":"acquire this special relationship\nwith the rest of the universe?"},{"time":532072,"text":"Well, one thing that's true\nabout Stephen Hawking's remark --"},{"time":536914,"text":"I mean, it is true,\nbut it's the wrong emphasis."},{"time":540913,"text":"One thing that's true about it is that\nit doesn't do it with any special physics,"},{"time":546926,"text":"there's no special dispensation,\nno miracles involved."},{"time":549941,"text":"It does it simply with three things\nthat we have here in abundance."},{"time":554000,"text":"One of them is matter,"},{"time":555674,"text":"because the growth of knowledge\nis a form of information processing."},{"time":560754,"text":"Information processing is computation,\ncomputation requires a computer --"},{"time":564715,"text":"there's no known way of making\na computer without matter."},{"time":567738,"text":"We also need energy to make\nthe computer, and most important,"},{"time":571237,"text":"to make the media, in effect,\nonto which we record"},{"time":575231,"text":"the knowledge that we discover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577000,"text":"And then thirdly,\nless tangible but just as essential"},{"time":581165,"text":"for the open-ended creation\nof knowledge, of explanations,"},{"time":585387,"text":"is evidence."},{"time":589142,"text":"Now, our environment\nis inundated with evidence."},{"time":592347,"text":"We happen to get round to testing,\nlet's say, Newton's Law of Gravity,"},{"time":598000,"text":"about 300 years ago."},{"time":599753,"text":"But the evidence that we used to do that"},{"time":603116,"text":"was falling down on every\nsquare meter of the Earth"},{"time":606429,"text":"for billions of years before that,"},{"time":608106,"text":"and will continue to fall\nfor billions of years afterwards."},{"time":612484,"text":"And the same is true\nfor all the other sciences."},{"time":615000,"text":"As far as we know, evidence to discover\nthe most fundamental truths"},{"time":620000,"text":"of all the sciences is here just\nfor the taking, on our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624298,"text":"Our location is saturated with evidence"},{"time":627186,"text":"and also with matter and energy."},{"time":629642,"text":"Out in intergalactic space,"},{"time":631904,"text":"those three prerequisites\nfor the open-ended creation of knowledge"},{"time":635317,"text":"are at their lowest possible supply --"},{"time":637761,"text":"as I said, it's empty, it's cold\nand it's dark out there."},{"time":642496,"text":"Or is it?"},{"time":644236,"text":"Now actually, that's just\nanother parochial misconception."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647970,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649069,"text":"Because imagine a cube out there\nin intergalactic space,"},{"time":654064,"text":"the same size as our home,\nthe solar system."},{"time":657749,"text":"Now that cube is very empty\nby human standards,"},{"time":661000,"text":"but that still means that it contains\nover a million tons of matter."},{"time":666000,"text":"And a million tons is enough to make,\nsay, a self-contained space station,"},{"time":671000,"text":"on which there's a colony of scientists"},{"time":673374,"text":"that are devoted to creating an open-ended\nstream of knowledge, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677799,"text":"Now, it's way beyond present technology"},{"time":679908,"text":"to even gather the hydrogen\nfrom intergalactic space"},{"time":684058,"text":"and form it into other elements and so on."},{"time":687872,"text":"But the thing is,\nin a comprehensible universe,"},{"time":690824,"text":"if something isn't forbidden\nby the laws of physics,"},{"time":694214,"text":"then what could possibly prevent us\nfrom doing it, other than knowing how?"},{"time":698383,"text":"In other words, it's a matter\nof knowledge, not resources."},{"time":701784,"text":"If we could do that, we'd automatically\nhave an energy supply,"},{"time":705419,"text":"because this transmutation\nwould be a fusion reactor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708887,"text":"And evidence?"},{"time":710648,"text":"Well, again, it's dark out there\nto human senses,"},{"time":713847,"text":"but all you've got to do\nis take a telescope,"},{"time":715990,"text":"even one of present-day design,"},{"time":718157,"text":"look out, and you'll see\nthe same galaxies as we do from here."},{"time":722597,"text":"And with a more powerful telescope,"},{"time":724967,"text":"you'll be able to see stars\nand planets in those galaxies,"},{"time":727713,"text":"you'll be able to do astrophysics\nand learn the laws of physics."},{"time":731147,"text":"And locally there you could build\nparticle accelerators,"},{"time":733811,"text":"and learn elementary particle physics\nand chemistry, and so on."},{"time":737072,"text":"Probably the hardest science to do\nwould be biology field trips --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":741554,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":742895,"text":"because it would take\nseveral hundred million years"},{"time":745858,"text":"to get to the nearest\nlife-bearing planet and back."},{"time":749201,"text":"But I have to tell you --\nand sorry, Richard --"},{"time":751507,"text":"but I never did like biology\nfield trips much,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":754865,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":756197,"text":"and I think we can just about make do"},{"time":758217,"text":"with one every few hundred million years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760341,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762382,"text":"So in fact, intergalactic space\ndoes contain all the prerequisites"},{"time":769362,"text":"for the open-ended creation of knowledge."},{"time":772250,"text":"Any such cube anywhere in the universe"},{"time":775450,"text":"could become the same kind\nof hub that we are,"},{"time":780059,"text":"if the knowledge of how to do so\nwere present there."},{"time":785758,"text":"So, we're not in a uniquely\nhospitable place."},{"time":789170,"text":"If intergalactic space\nis capable of creating"},{"time":791708,"text":"an open-ended stream of explanations,"},{"time":794318,"text":"then so is almost every other environment,"},{"time":796509,"text":"so is the Earth."},{"time":797763,"text":"So is a polluted Earth."},{"time":800474,"text":"And the limiting factor, there and here,"},{"time":804210,"text":"is not resources,\nbecause they're plentiful,"},{"time":807090,"text":"but knowledge, which is scarce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809610,"text":"Now this cosmic knowledge-based view\nmay -- and I think ought to --"},{"time":815603,"text":"make us feel very special."},{"time":817943,"text":"But it should also\nmake us feel vulnerable,"},{"time":820585,"text":"because it means that\nwithout the specific knowledge"},{"time":824024,"text":"that's needed to survive\nthe ongoing challenges of the universe,"},{"time":827795,"text":"we won't survive them."},{"time":829000,"text":"All it takes is for a supernova\nto go off a few light-years away,"},{"time":832509,"text":"and we'll all be dead!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834254,"text":"Martin Rees has recently written a book"},{"time":836677,"text":"about our vulnerability\nto all sorts of things,"},{"time":840000,"text":"from astrophysics, to scientific\nexperiments gone wrong,"},{"time":844000,"text":"and most importantly, to terrorism\nwith weapons of mass destruction."},{"time":848374,"text":"And he thinks that civilization\nhas only a 50 percent chance"},{"time":851825,"text":"of surviving this century."},{"time":853276,"text":"I think he's going to talk\nabout that later in the conference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856435,"text":"Now, I don't think that probability\nis the right category"},{"time":861607,"text":"to discuss this issue in,"},{"time":863000,"text":"but I do agree with him about this:"},{"time":864759,"text":"We can survive and we can fail to survive."},{"time":869502,"text":"But it depends not on chance,"},{"time":872271,"text":"but on whether we create\nthe relevant knowledge in time."},{"time":876000,"text":"The danger is not at all unprecedented."},{"time":878826,"text":"Species go extinct all the time."},{"time":882071,"text":"Civilizations end."},{"time":884253,"text":"The overwhelming majority\nof all species and all civilizations"},{"time":887713,"text":"that have ever existed are now history."},{"time":890322,"text":"And if we want to be\nthe exception to that,"},{"time":893220,"text":"then logically, our only hope\nis to make use of the one feature"},{"time":899143,"text":"that distinguishes our species\nand civilization from all the others --"},{"time":903791,"text":"namely, our special relationship\nwith the laws of physics,"},{"time":908262,"text":"our ability to create\nnew explanations, new knowledge --"},{"time":912759,"text":"to be a hub of existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915919,"text":"So let me now apply this\nto a current controversy,"},{"time":919663,"text":"not because I want to advocate\nany particular solution,"},{"time":922902,"text":"but just to illustrate\nthe kind of thing I mean."},{"time":925560,"text":"And the controversy is global warming."},{"time":928000,"text":"Now, I'm a physicist,\nbut I'm not the right kind of physicist."},{"time":931029,"text":"In regard to global warming,\nI'm just a layman."},{"time":934787,"text":"And the rational thing for a layman to do"},{"time":937642,"text":"is to take seriously\nthe prevailing scientific theory."},{"time":942167,"text":"And according to that theory,\nit's already too late to avoid a disaster,"},{"time":946858,"text":"because if it's true that our best option\nat the moment is to prevent CO2 emissions"},{"time":952650,"text":"with something like the Kyoto Protocol,"},{"time":954544,"text":"with its constraints on economic activity\nand its enormous cost"},{"time":958385,"text":"of hundreds of billions of dollars,\nor whatever it is,"},{"time":961000,"text":"then that is already a disaster\nby any reasonable measure."},{"time":966382,"text":"And the actions that are advocated are not\neven purported to solve the problem,"},{"time":971475,"text":"merely to postpone it by a little."},{"time":973879,"text":"So it's already too late to avoid it,"},{"time":975688,"text":"and it probably has been\ntoo late to avoid it"},{"time":978596,"text":"ever since before anyone\nrealized the danger."},{"time":982441,"text":"It was probably already\ntoo late in the 1970s,"},{"time":985529,"text":"when the best available\nscientific theory was telling us"},{"time":988748,"text":"that industrial emissions were\nabout to precipitate a new ice age,"},{"time":992286,"text":"in which billions would die."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995312,"text":"Now, the lesson of that seems clear to me,"},{"time":997495,"text":"and I don't know why it isn't\ninforming public debate."},{"time":1001106,"text":"It is that we can't always know."},{"time":1004436,"text":"When we know of an impending disaster,"},{"time":1007094,"text":"and how to solve it at a cost less\nthan the cost of the disaster itself,"},{"time":1011720,"text":"then there's not going to be\nmuch argument, really."},{"time":1014616,"text":"But no precautions\nand no precautionary principle"},{"time":1019209,"text":"can avoid problems\nthat we do not yet foresee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023982,"text":"Hence, we need a stance of problem-fixing,"},{"time":1028444,"text":"not just problem-avoidance."},{"time":1031712,"text":"And it's true that an ounce of prevention\nequals a pound of cure,"},{"time":1035120,"text":"but that's only if we know\nwhat to prevent."},{"time":1038072,"text":"If you've been punched on the nose,"},{"time":1040057,"text":"then the science of medicine\ndoes not consist of teaching you"},{"time":1043216,"text":"how to avoid punches."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044598,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045637,"text":"If medical science stopped seeking cures\nand concentrated on prevention only,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"then it would achieve\nvery little of either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053771,"text":"The world is buzzing at the moment"},{"time":1055820,"text":"with plans to force reductions\nin gas emissions at all costs."},{"time":1060950,"text":"It ought to be buzzing with plans\nto reduce the temperature,"},{"time":1065253,"text":"and with plans to live\nat the higher temperature --"},{"time":1068288,"text":"and not at all costs,\nbut efficiently and cheaply."},{"time":1071532,"text":"And some such plans exist,"},{"time":1072883,"text":"things like swarms of mirrors in space\nto deflect the sunlight away,"},{"time":1077119,"text":"and encouraging aquatic organisms\nto eat more carbon dioxide."},{"time":1081000,"text":"At the moment, these things\nare fringe research;"},{"time":1084312,"text":"they're not central to the human effort\nto face this problem,"},{"time":1088041,"text":"or problems in general."},{"time":1090000,"text":"And with problems\nthat we are not aware of yet,"},{"time":1092795,"text":"the ability to put right -- not the sheer\ngood luck of avoiding indefinitely --"},{"time":1098978,"text":"is our only hope, not just\nof solving problems,"},{"time":1101795,"text":"but of survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103671,"text":"So take two stone tablets,\nand carve on them."},{"time":1111057,"text":"On one of them, carve:\n\"Problems are soluble.\""},{"time":1115763,"text":"And on the other one, carve:\n\"Problems are inevitable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1120396,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121579,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}